"title": "5877: hesitation",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5877",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A delay in reaching a decision, or a reluctance to reach a decision, on account of uncertainty, caution or rebellion. Scripture provides examples of individuals who hesitate in the face of divine commands or promises, and indicates its dangers.</p>\n<h2>Examples of people who hesitated</h2>\n<h3>Lot</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen19:16\">GEN 19:16</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Lot's wife</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen19:26\">GEN 19:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen19:17\">GEN 19:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:32\">LUK 17:32</a></p>\n<h3>Moses</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:11\">EXO 3:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:13\">EXO 3:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod4:1\">EXO 4:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod4:10\">EXO 4:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod4:13\">EXO 4:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod6:12\">EXO 6:12</a></p>\n<h3>Peter in obeying the Lord</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:12\">ACT 11:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:14-Acts10:20\">ACT 10:14–10:20</a></p>\n<h3>Other examples</h3>\n<p>Israel on approaching the promised land:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num13:31-Num13:33\">NUM 13:31–13:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:1-Num14:4\">NUM 14:1–14:4</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:36-Judg6:40\">JDG 6:36–6:40</a> <em>Gideon</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:21\">1KI 18:21</a> <em>Israel in the time of Elijah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer1:6\">JER 1:6</a> <em>Jeremiah</em></p>\n<h2>Examples of people who did not hesitate</h2>\n<h3>Caleb</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num13:30\">NUM 13:30</a></p>\n<h3>Simon and Andrew</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:18-Matt4:20\">MAT 4:18–4:20</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:16-Mark1:18\">MRK 1:16–1:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:10-Luke5:11\">LUK 5:10–5:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:40-John1:42\">JHN 1:40–1:42</a></p>\n<h3>Paul</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:27\">ACT 20:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:20\">ACT 20:20</a></p>\n<h2>Believers should not hesitate to act when they know what is right</h2>\n<h3>They should not hesitate to speak</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa58:1\">ISA 58:1</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ commands immediate obedience</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:62\">LUK 9:62</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:57-Luke9:60\">LUK 9:57–9:60</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:19-Matt8:22\">MAT 8:19–8:22</a></p>\n<h2>God does not hesitate</h2>\n<h3>To bring judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek24:14\">EZK 24:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek12:25\">EZK 12:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:14\">DAN 9:14</a></p>\n<h3>The delay in Jesus Christ's return is not due to hesitation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:9\">2PE 3:9</a></strong></p>",
